You are here: SALESFORCE HELP DOCS INSURANCE Insurance Group Benefits Small Group Quoting

Small group quoting is a process to market and sell insurance to small group employers. Quotes are generated based on customer preferences and premium costs calculated from variables like employee count, dependents, geography, required coverages, and employer contributions. The quotes are presented for acceptance.

Insurance plans let small groups sell standard insurance and ancillary products, helping get leads for brokers or sales representatives. This also helps increase control and compliance over the sales process and lower acquisition cost.

Internal sales representatives can use the Insurance quoting process to sell directly to small group employers, managing assigned accounts and using opportunities with quotes to sell one or more insurance or ancillary products.

Vlocity Insurance has services to facilitate a comprehensive quote-to-contract workflow for Small Group quotes. Templates are provided for new and renewal quotes, which can be used in OmniScripts to display multiple Small Group rated insurance plans.
